  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Organisation d&apos;Appui &#xE0; l&apos;auto Promotion</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The 3 partners of oxfam will intervene in 3 provinces namely Cibitoke, Bubanza and Bujumbura Rural within the 9 communes on 18 pilot hills. The OAP partner will intervene in Bujumbura Rural province in Kabezi, Kanyosha and Muhuta communes on 6 hills. It will workwith 1,500 direct beneficiaries (50% men and 50% women) and indirectly with 45,000 households (15,000 households / commune).
The project also aims to focus its actions strategically on the main theme of climate change and greenhouse gas reduction, by integrating in a complementary and continuous way the development actions implemented by OAP in the province of Bujumbura. This helps to ensure from the beginning of the project a legitimacy of partner actions in the target hills, but also to facilitate the organization of local environmental governance committees on climate change and their acceptance at the local level.</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org role="4" type="24">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">O.A.P.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;O.A.P. &quot; (Organisation d&apos;appui &#xE0; l&apos;Autopromotion)
 is a burundian local development NGO.
Its overall objective is to contribute tothe improvement of the socio-economic and political conditions for rural populations through the support of communities intheir development efforts.
It vision is a world of social justice where poverty has been eradicated, a life in dignity and security. OAP#s  is committed to working in partnership with other stakeholders to address the root causes of rural poverty, raiseawareness, contribute to peace building, and thus improve the living conditions of communities. Implementation strategies are  based on a deep understanding of the needs of the target populations as they are invited to participate in the development and execution of projects.
Strategies that help achieve the objectives include: client orientation, capacity building for women and youth, potential forces for rural development, as well as other marginalized groups; institutional capacity building of OAP, useof sport and cultural events#. OAP hasbeen implementing projects in Burundi (province of Bujumbura rural) with the support of Oxfam affiliates.
For instance, OAP was involved in the implementation of the Peace beyond Borders program from  2012 -2015 with the support of Oxfam Novib. Equally, since 3 years, OAP implemented a project to support ex-combatants with the support of Oxfam Germany, to mention a few.
In this program ARC-Nyubahiriza, OAP will implement activities under outcome 1 and 2 in the province of Bujumbura rural.</narrative>
  </participating-org>
